Class FormattedPageIOOptions<T extends FormattedPageIOOptions<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.tms.api.io.BaseIOOptions<T>
      • org.tms.api.io.StyledPageIOOptions<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of BaseIOOptions in this FormattedPageIOOptions
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    DateTimeFormatIOOption, PageableIOOption, StyleableIOOption, TitleableIOOption
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DocOptions, PDFOptions, RTFOptions

    public abstract class FormattedPageIOOptions<T extends FormattedPageIOOptions<T>>
extends TitledPageIOOptions<FormattedPageIOOptions<T>>
implements DateTimeFormatIOOption, PageableIOOption
    The base class that BaseIOOptions that support formatted and paged export output. Format and paging elements that are supported include:
    • page width,
    • page height,
    • page numbers,
    • paging,
    • sticky row labels,
    • sticky columns labels, and
    • date-time format pattern for page footers.

    Note: FormattedPageIOOptions methods only affect export operations.

    Since:
    "1.1"
    Version:
    "1.1"
    See Also:
    FormattedPageIOOptions, PageableIOOption

      • withDateTimeFormat

        public T withDateTimeFormat(String pattern)
        Set the date-time format pattern to use to display the time and date the in the page footnotes of the export. The date-time format pattern follows the conventions described in SimpleDateFormat. To disable the display of the date-time in page footers, set pattern to null.

        The default value is MM/dd/yyyy hh:mm a

        Parameters:
        pattern - the new date-time format pattern or null to disable
        Returns:
        a new T with the date-time format pattern set
        See Also:
        SimpleDateFormat

      • withPages

        public T withPages()
        Enable paged output in exports. Table data is output in discrete pages, optionally, with column headings repeated on the top of each page, and page numbers and the date-time that the export was performed output on the bottom of each page.
        Returns:
        a new T with output paging enabled
        See Also:
        withDateTimeFormat, withPageNumbers, withStickyColumnLabels

      • withPages

        public T withPages(boolean enabled)
        Enable or disable paged output in exports. When true, Table data is output in discrete pages, optionally, with column headings repeated on the top of each page, and page numbers and the date-time that the export was performed output on the bottom of each page. When false, the output is not paged.
        Parameters:
        enabled - true to enable paging, false to disable paging
        Returns:
        a new T with output paging enabled or disabled
        See Also:
        withDateTimeFormat, withPageNumbers, withStickyColumnLabels
